randoop.util

Class ReflectionExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • randoop.util.ReflectionExecutor

  • public final class ReflectionExecutor
extends java.lang.Object
    Static methods that execute the code of a ReflectionCode object.

    If a test exceeds the timeout, it is canceled and reported as a timeout. When --usethreads is true, each test is run on a separate thread, in parallel but not in isolation (that is, not starting from a fresh JVM).

    • Field Detail

      • usethreads

        public static boolean usethreads
        If true, Randoop executes each test in a separate thread and kills tests that take too long to finish, as determined by the --call-timeout-millis command-line argument. Tests killed in this manner are not reported to the user, but are recorded in Randoop's log. Use the --log command-line option to make Randoop produce the log.

        Use this option if Randoop does not terminate, which is usually due to execution of code under test that results in an infinite loop or that waits for user input. The downside of this option is a BIG (order-of-magnitude) decrease in generation speed. The tests are run in parallel, but not in isolation.

      • timed_out_tests

        public static org.plumelib.util.FileWriterWithName timed_out_tests
        If specified, Randoop logs timed-out tests to the specified file. Has no effect unless the --usethreads command-line option is given.

      • CALL_TIMEOUT_MILLIS_DEFAULT

        public static int CALL_TIMEOUT_MILLIS_DEFAULT
        Default for call_timeout_millis, in milliseconds. Should only be accessed by checkOptionsValid().

      • call_timeout_millis

        public static int call_timeout_millis
